        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 2:49PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 249 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gilbertsville, or 7 miles east of Norwich, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsfield, New Lisbon, New Berlin, Morris, Gilbertsville, Lathams
Corners, Holmesville, South New Berlin, and South Edmeston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
